  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The BLOCKHASH implementation is inefficient which can potentially lead to DoS from a malicious miner.\n\nA malicious miner can create a contract that calls BLOCKHASH multiple times, taking up processing time in the Go client for a gas cost that may be low enough for the miner to benefit from it by taking advantage of of the time other miners process the tx.\n\nThis can be resolved by caching the hashes of the last 256 blocks to get constant lookup of block hash given a block number.\n",
